One of the best tower defense games out there, & I've played literally hundreds & have ludicrously high standards.  More complex than the first, with a much greater emphasis on enemy type (live/magic/machine). New towers & enemies, but still has everything that made the first one great; great graphics, alchemy/runes, persistent upgrades, open maps, good number of enemies & towers, Sphere of Creation, enemy intelligence scaling with difficulty, awards that when earned permanently increase how much glory points you get, & the 'interactive' help menu with info on all enemies & towers.  In addition to bringing all the above back from the first game, this game also has even better graphics, much longer & overall better campaigns, less waves in relationship to hardness (the main negative of the first, in my opinion, was the very large number of waves per game, especially in the higher hardness levels), & a number of minor UI improvements.  Those improvements aside, I personally feel the first game was overall better. It had a more balanced selection of towers, as this game heavily emphasises enemy type, with too many towers only able to attack one enemy type (& yet no anti-magic towers, for some reason). Also, the last game has NO FROST MAGES, making it a better game by default. The Frost Mage ability to go through one tower puts a huge damper on things for me, forcing me to make short, thick mazes instead of the long, creative ones I like to make.  Overall, it is still a great game, & still easily one of my favorites.
